<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="95" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/250: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">House</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-15T23:00:00+00:00">November 15, 1918—11
                                    p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 15—7:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>110. For the President. I have just received the following communication
                            from <persName>Lord Derby</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Copy of telegram from Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> to <persName>Lord Derby</persName> of
                                    November 15th. Very urgent. Personal. Please convey following
                                    message from the King to <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel
                                        House</persName> for transmission to the President of the
                                    United States. ‘I am delighted to hear that you contemplate
                                    shortly coming to England on your way to France. It would give
                                    the Queen and myself the greatest pleasure if you and Mrs.
                                        <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName> will be our
                                    guests at Buckingham Palace during your stay in London.’”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>